<h1>Post</h1>

<p><img src="https://static.raymondcamden.com/images/cfjedi/Adobe_Flash_Builder_4_Logo.png" align="left" /> Just a quick note to let folks know Adobe has updated Flash Builder 4.5 today to add support for iOS and Blackberry Playbook. This means you can now easily push out <b>one</b> project to all three platforms - even on a Windows device. (I did this myself.) For more details, check out these two blog posts:</p>
<p><a href="http://blogs.adobe.com/flashplatform/2011/06/build-mobile-apps-for-android-devices-blackberry-playbook-iphone-and-ipad-today.html">Build Mobile Apps for Android Devices, BlackBerry PlayBook, iPhone and iPad Today!</a></p>
<p><a href="http://gregsramblings.com/2011/06/20/finally-its-here-flex-on-ios-android-and-blackberry-playbook/">FINALLY – it's here – Flex on iOS, Android, and BlackBerry PlayBook</a></p>
<p>I'm going to have an iPad pretty soon and once I can - I'll report on how well the process works.</p>
<p>As a reminder - I'll be talking about Flash Builder and ColdFusion this week - Thursday at 5PM. You can sign up for free <a href="http://www.adobe.com/cfusion/event/index.cfm?event=detail&id=1489921&loc=en_us">here</a>.</p>
